{
  "texts": [
    "The non-rapid eye movement (NREM) sleep time (p < 0.01) and the percentage of non-rapid eye movement (NREM) sleep stage 2 of the intervention group were significantly increased (p < 0.05) after the intervention.",
    "However, no other significant change was observed (Table 5).",
    "This study aimed to evaluate the influence of Tai Chi exercise on sleep quality of elderly population using both subjective and objective measures.",
    "Our research hypothesis was broadly verified, indicating that Tai Chi exercise may positively change both subjective and objective sleep quality among the normal elderly population.",
    "Specifically, scores on the Pittsburgh Sleep Quality Index and Insomnia Severity Index, but not on the Narcolepsy Scale, were significantly decreased following the exercise intervention (based on the comparisons between groups)."
  ]
}